        "section_value": "Chief Complaint\nElevated blood sugars requiring further investigation and medication adjustment.\nHistory of Present Illness\nNatalie is a 39-year-old female presenting for a check-up following elevated lab results. She reports experiencing no symptoms of hyperglycemia, but her recent blood sugars were high. She's currently taking 1000mg of metformin daily and monitoring her blood sugars at home. She reports a diet focused on avoiding sugars and regular power walking (approximately 30 minutes daily). She has an ACL repair from five years ago and reports no issues with her knee. Her blood pressure is well-controlled on lisinopril, and she monitors it at home.\nFindings\nPhysical exam reveals a systolic ejection murmur of approximately 3/6. Lung sounds are clear bilaterally. The abdomen is soft and non-tender. Extremities are warm and well perfused. No swelling is noted. Her oxygen saturation is 98% on room air.\nAssessment\nThe patient presents with hyperglycemia, as evidenced by an elevated A1c of 8.1%. This requires further investigation and adjustment of her current medication regimen.\nPlan",
